  "prompt": "What are the symptoms of a bad speed sensor?",
  "response": "A bad speed sensor can cause various issues in a vehicle. Some common symptoms include:\n\n1. **Check Engine Light**: If the speed sensor is malfunctioning, the vehicle's computer may detect the issue, causing the check engine light to illuminate.\n\n2. **Erratic Speedometer**: The speedometer may behave unpredictably, displaying incorrect speed readings or fluctuating wildly.\n\n3. **Transmission Problems**: A faulty speed sensor can affect the shifting of gears. You might notice rough or delayed shifting, or the transmission may get stuck in a single gear.\n\n4. **Cruise Control Issues**: Many vehicles utilize speed sensors for cruise control functionality. A malfunctioning sensor can cause cruise control to stop working or work inconsistently.\n\n5. **Reduced Fuel Efficiency**: The lack of accurate speed data can lead the engine control unit to make incorrect adjustments, potentially reducing fuel efficiency.\n\n6. **ABS Warning Light**: In vehicles equipped with anti-lock brake systems (ABS), the speed sensor can affect the system's operation, leading to an ABS warning light on the dashboard.\n\n7. **Loss of Power**: The vehicle might experience intermittent power loss, especially during acceleration.\n\nIf you suspect your vehicle's speed sensor is faulty, it's important to have it checked and replaced by a professional mechanic to avoid further mechanical issues.",
